  "prompt": "How do I filter out US election news in my Quora feed?",
  "response": "Filtering out specific topics like US election news on Quora involves several steps to customize your feed. Here's how you can do it:\n\n1. **Unfollow Topics**:\n   - Go to your profile by clicking on your profile picture.\n   - Click on the \"Following\" tab.\n   - In the \"Topics\" section, find and unfollow topics related to US elections (e.g., \"US Politics,\" \"Election 2024,\" \"Democratic Party,\" \"Republican Party,\" etc.).\n\n2. **Mute Specific Questions**:\n   - If a question related to US elections appears in your feed, you can mute it.\n   - Click on the three dots (ellipsis) next to the question.\n   - Select \"Mute Question\" from the dropdown menu.\n\n3. **Adjust Your Interests**:\n   - Visit your settings by clicking on your profile picture and then the \"Settings\" option.\n   - In \"Account Settings,\" find \"Interests\" and adjust them to focus more on other topics you are interested in.\n\n4. **Report/Inappropriate Content**:\n   - If you feel certain content is inappropriate or disruptive, you can report it to Quora.\n   - Click on the three dots next to the content and select \"Report\" from the dropdown menu.\n\n5. **Use Browser Extensions**:\n   - There are browser extensions available that can help filter content. For example, extensions like \"Social Fixer\" for Facebook can be customized for Quora to filter out keywords related to US elections.\n\nBy following these steps and continually managing your feed, you can reduce the frequency of seeing US election news and tailor your Quora experience to be more in line with your preferences.",
